# 14. Real-World CI/CD Example

---

# Scenario

Production deployment should happen only when:

* Branch = main
* Event = push
* Tests passed

---

# Workflow

```yaml
name: Production CI/CD

on:
  push:
  pull_request:

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - run: echo "Running tests"

  deploy:
    needs: test

    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' &&
        github.event_name == 'push'

    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - run: echo "Deploying to production"
```

---

# Workflow Logic

| Condition   | Required |
| ----------- | -------- |
| Tests pass  | ✅        |
| Branch main | ✅        |
| Push event  | ✅        |

---

# 15. Advanced Example

```yaml
name: Advanced Conditional Workflow

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
      - develop

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - run: echo "Build Started"

      - name: Main Deployment
        if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'

        run: echo "Production Deployment"

      - name: Development Deployment
        if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/develop'

        run: echo "Development Deployment"

      - name: Always Run
        if: always()

        run: echo "Cleanup completed"
```

